[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glasgow police find ex-soldier after appeal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have traced a missing former soldier after an appeal following the discovery of his car in the centre of Glasgow.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
James Spence, 47, who served with the Scots Guards, has suffered from Post Traumatic Stress Disorder.
He left his home in Easterhill Road in Glasgow's Tollcross at 03:00 on Friday.
His car, a blue Vauxhall Tigra, was spotted in Yorkhill Street later.
